        <p>Terms and Conditions apply.<br>
            Conditions of Entry - SKYPARK OBSERVATION DECK ENTRY TO THE SKYPARK OBSERVATION DECK IS SUBJECT TO THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS:
            <ul>
                <li>Sands SkyPark Observation Deck is subject to inclement weather. If rain or lightning is present, then the SkyPark Observation Deck may be closed. Only guests that have been up to the SkyPark Observation Deck for less than one (1) hour when it is closed are entitled to a refund. Management reserves the right to close the SkyPark Observation Deck as they deem necessary.</li>
                <li>Entry to the SkyPark Observation Deck is subject to availability - wait time to enter will be based upon based upon Observation Deck capacity.</li>
                <li>Tickets are for single entry only.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>PROHIBITED ITEMS
            <ul>
                <li>Admission time is strictly observed. Late arrival may result in non-admittance until suitable availability at the Museum’s discretion.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>PROHIBITED ITEMS<br>
            The following items are PROHIBITED and therefore not permitted on the SkyPark Observation Deck:
            <ul>
                <li>Luggage, professional photographic equipment and professional video-recording equipment (such as tripods, lights and reflectors), pre-purchased food 
                    and beverages (lightsnacks are available for purchase at The SkyPark), glass bottles, aluminium cans, pets (only service animals are permitted),     aerosol cans, firearms, knives (including pocket knives), box cutters or weapons of any kind, chairs, picnic blankets, signs or weapons of any kind, 
                    chairs, picnic blankets, signs, sticks, poles, laser pointers, whistles air horns, bull horns, fireworks, illegal substances/narcotics, pepper spray, mace and 
                    any item deemed by management to be dangerous or inappropriate.</li>
                <li>Entry to the SkyPark Observation Deck is subject to availability - wait time to enter  based upon Observation Deck capacity.</li>
                <li>Prohibited items, excluding pets, weapons and illegal substances/narcotics, may be checked with the Guest Service Desk located at the Porte Cochere    of Tower 3. Items may be subject to physical or electronic security screening.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>





